doc_summary_long: Officer sues Wal-Mart for firing him for carrying gun while working as police officer A Pennsylvania police officer is suing Wal-Mart after he says he was fired for carrying his police-issued gun while in the store. While in uniform and on-duty, Michael Zuby said he stopped by the Wal-Mart store where he was employed to grab some lunch.
